<P>
   MONEYTALK _ When Securities and Exchange Commission Chairman
Arthur Levitt talked recently about electronic investing in the
next century, he summoned up the old-fashioned wisdom of folk
singer Pete Seeger: ``Education is when you read the fine print.
Experience is what you get when you don't.'' His point was that
successful investing will always require detailed and demanding
study. Some tips for investors. (Ezell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   PETERPAN-TOUR _ Atlanta Ballet will tour new $2.5 million
production of ``Peter Pan,'' much reconfigured from version it did
here in 1997, to London in December. New sets, costumes by noted
South African designer. It will play 28 performances in 21 days at
Royal Festival Hall in the South Bank arts complex. BBC
Philharmonic in the pit with Robert Chumbley conducting. $87,000
grant from the Katherine John Murphy Foundation is the enabling
money. (Green, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
