   ROSENFELD-SHORTTAKES _ Hillary Clinton has formed an exploratory
committee to advise her whether to run for U.S. Senate in New York.
The committee will tell her it's OK. When was the last time you saw
an exploratory committee say the mere idea is a nightmare?
Exploratory committees, in their simplicity, want to give their
hearts away. (Rosenfeld, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ The recent common-sense Supreme Court ruling on
schoolhouse sexual harassment has driven even normally sane
conservatives into great curlicues of loopiness, composed in about
equal parts of ridicule, outrage and panic. (Tom Teepen is national
correspondent for Cox Newspapers.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ Perhaps it's time to take another, softer
look at pork barrel politics, that long-deprecated practice of
Washington lawmakers bringing the bacon to the folks back home. We
deserve the money back, after all. (Howard Kleinberg is a columnist
for Cox News Service.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ One of my favorite pieces of
reading material is a raggedy little paperback book I keep in the
desk drawer next to the stationery. It's titled: ``The Standard
Cyclopaedia of Useful Knowledge.'' This is the November, 1896
issue. When life needs simplifying, I pull it out and read.
(Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
