<P>
   SUPER: The Kansas City school board could get its first look
Thursday at a handful of candidates for superintendent. Among them
is a dynamic official in the U.S. Department of Education who has
served as a teacher, principal and state superintendent of
instruction. Photo. Phil O'Connor. 25.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE: President Clinton today won pledges from thousands of
movie theaters to require photo identification from young people
seeking admission to R-rated movies. Clinton had challenged the
industry to enforce the rating system more strictly in the wake of
the high school shootings in Littleton, Colo. In response, the
National Association of Theater Owners said it would adopt a new
policy requiring youths unaccompanied by adults to produce a photo
ID before being admitted to R-rated films. The association
represents about 20,000 screens _ 65 percent of the motion picture
screens in the United States. We'll talk to kids, parents and other
experts _ including AMC Theaters _ about whether they think this
will really work and whether it can be enforced. Donald Bradley.
30. Photo.
