   GUNDEAL _ WASHINGTON _ One percent of the nation's gun dealers
sold nearly half of the guns used in crime last year and many of
those businesses show up year after year as major sources of crime
weapons, according to a new study of federal firearms data. The
study conducted by the office of Sen. Charles E. Schumer, D-N.Y.,
marks a new phase of a growing effort to hold firearms dealers
responsible for gun violence. Georgia ranks high on the list as a
supplier of guns used in crime. (Foskett, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
