   STUN-BELTS _ WASHINGTON _ Retired police detective Frank Serpico
joins the daughter of Muhammad Ali at an Amnesty International news
conference to release a new report on the stun belt, a widely used
law enforcement device that Amnesty says is ``potentially lethal to
people with heart ailments, epilepsy or on tranquilizers.'' (Hill,
Cox News Service). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   CHILD-CARE _ WASHINGTON _ Child care advocates say that a report
they'll release Tuesday afternoon, endorsed by Education Secretary
Richard Riley, will show that ``quality'' child care helps kids in
early learning and school readiness. Past studies by others have
been ambiguous. (Mollison, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   CHILD-CARE-TIPS _ Child care information tips. (Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ Microsoft attorneys cross-examine Garry
Norris, an IBM executive who offered damaging testimony in the
federal antitrust trial. (Glass, Cox News Service). 22.
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET BUDGET INFORMATION FOR SUBSCRIBERS OF THE NYT NEWS
SERVICE
</P>
<P>
   Spot news budgets move daily at 2 p.m. and 6 p.m. Eastern.
Additionally, separate features and commentary budgets move at 10
a.m., and sports and business budgets at 6 p.m. Additional updates
are possible if news developments warrant.
</P>
<P>
   All times are Eastern unless otherwise noted. If stories will
move after 8 p.m., an ETA will be given.
</P>
