<P>
   HKN-SABRES-STARS (Dallas) _ Buffalo at Dallas, 8 p.m., in Game 1
of the Stanley Cup finals. By Joe LaPointe.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-VECSEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ On Mark Jackson and Chris Mullin,
the two wise, old Indiana Pacers who grew up in New York City,
played college ball in New York City and have more of that city
savvy than anyone on the Knicks. By George Vecsey.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SPREWELL-COMPANY (Rosemont, Pa.) _ In the cluttered
Rosemont, Pa.-based offices of And 1, Latrell Sprewell is a deity,
the apotheosis of the manic playground ``baller'' and the poster
boy for a trash-talking company geared to selling solely basketball
footwear and apparel to hoops-mad teenagers. The company, begun
five years ago by three guys in their 20s with student loans as
their sole financing, has garnered huge notice with its Sprewell
``American Dream'' commercial. By Richard Sandomir.
</P>
<P>
   BKL-WNBA (Undated) _ Many WNBA players agree that the process of
insuring labor peace and jobs for the next four years was a lot
rougher than they expected. Nearly three months of bargaining
revealed a novice, inexperienced union at odds with itself, its
leadership and management, insecure in the knowledge that it stood
to lose as much as it might gain.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKS-PHILLIES (Philadephia) _ Yanks at Philadelphia, 7:35
p.m. By Buster Olney.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-METS-BLUEJAYS (New York) _ Toronto at Mets, 7:40 p.m. By
Jack Curry.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-ANDERSON-COLUMN (Undated) _ On Ben Hogan and the U.S. Open,
which is just a week away. By Dave Anderson.
</P>
