<SLUG> BC-WINE-TASTINGS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WINE OF THE WEEK 
</HEADLINE>
  (jt) 
 By FRANK J. PRIAL    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Monthelie Les Champs Fulliots 1996, Bouchard Pere et Fils,
Burgundy. About $30.
</P>
<P>
   It's a good thing a few Monthelie wines are shipped to our
shores because finding them in Burgundy can be frustrating.
Monthelie is a quiet village and easy to miss. Monthelie is not a
famous wine but at its best it can be a fine Burgundy. Less
concentrated than a Volnay, perhaps, but fruity and delicious.
Rustic is a word often used to describe Monthelie, but in this case
it is better than that. The wine has good body and a lingering
finish, and shows the new emphasis on excellence at this venerable
Burgundy house.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
