   SHARP DRIVING _ The Jeep Wrangler is everything that a vehicle
shouldn't be and at the same time everything that a sport-utility
should be. (Sharp, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). Includes 1-column
color photograph of columnist.
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ When Securities and Exchange Commission Chairman
Arthur Levitt talked recently about electronic investing in the
next century, he summoned up the old-fashioned wisdom of folk
singer Pete Seeger: ``Education is when you read the fine print.
Experience is what you get when you don't.'' His point was that
successful investing will always require detailed and demanding
study. Some tips for investors. (Ezell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOLOGY
</P>
<P>
   TECHJOBS _ Another wy to look at figures just released by the
American Electronics Association shows just how important
technology industries are in Georgia. Georgia ranked 10 in number
of tech jobs, but if you look at how many jobs there are per 1,000
population, the ranking goes way up. There are 18 tech jobs per
1,000 population here. (Holsendolph, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
18.
</P>
<P>
   CABLE-ISP _ Portland ruling forces AT&AMP;T cable (formerly TCI) to
open its lines to competing ISP's such as MindSpring, AOL and
others. AT&AMP;T is expected to appeal the decision, but MindSpring's
Dave Baker says the ruling is a very important first step for ISPs
to gain access to cable wires and begin offering cable modem
service. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   SUPERCOMM09 _ Day two of the big shoe at the GWCC. Steve
Ballmer, the president of Microsoft, gives the keynote address.
Carly Fiorina, a group president at Lucent Technologies, also
speaks. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   w/ BALLMER-BOX _ Profile box of Microsoft President Steve
Ballmer to go with Ballmer supercomm story. (Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   SUPERCOMM-PRODUCTS _ roundup of new products and services
announed at Supercomm. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
