   CLINTON-MOVIES _ WASHINGTON _ President Clinton and theater
owners announce a policy that will require viewers of R-rated movie
to show photo identification to prove they are 17. (Shepard, Cox
News Service). 22.
</P>
<P>
   STUN-BELTS _ WASHINGTON _ Retired police detective Frank Serpico
joins the daughter of Muhammad Ali at an Amnesty International news
conference to release a new report on the stun belt, a widely used
law enforcement device that Amnesty says is ``potentially lethal to
people with heart ailments, epilepsy or on tranquilizers.'' (Hill,
Cox News Service). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   CHILD-CARE _ WASHINGTON _ Child care advocates say that a report
they'll release Tuesday afternoon, endorsed by Education Secretary
Richard Riley, will show that ``quality'' child care helps kids in
early learning and school readiness. Past studies by others have
been ambiguous. (Mollison, Cox News Service).
</P>
