   KOSOVO-DIPLOMACY-ASSESS (Cologne, Germany) _ Analysis on the
loopholes in the draft UN resolution agreed on Tuesday. By Jane
Perlez.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-RUSSIA (Moscow) _ How the Russian military tried to
sabotage Chernomyrdin's peace efforts. By Michael R. Gordon.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-SCENE (Kosovo Polje, Yugoslavia) _ Unlike Serbs who may
live in more isolated villages, Serbs who live only a few miles
from the capital, Pristina, are not ready to leave their homes and
businesses and begin new lives as refugees. ``This is holy Serbian
land,'' said Ljubisa Lazic, 53, a jovial telephone inspector. ``Our
churches and our graves are like a stop sign to us _ they don't let
us leave here. If we did, we would be damned anywhere in the world
we go, both us and our children.'' By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
<P>
