<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Profile box of Microsoft's Steve Ballmer
 &HT;    (EDS: Sidebar to SUPERCOMM09)
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Name: Steve Ballmer
</P>
<P>
   Age: 42
</P>
<P>
   Title: President, Microsoft Corp., Redmond, Wash.
</P>
<P>
   Education: BA Harvard University, applied math and economics
</P>
<P>
   Job Responsibilities: Help Microsoft develop strategic alliances
and take advantage of future growth opportunities. A major portion
of the job is talking up Microsoft's various products and services
to potential partners and skeptical analysts and critics.
</P>
<P>
   Biggest Challenge: Working with Microsoft chairman Bill Gates to
reinvent Microsoft for the 21st Century.
</P>
<P>
   Hobbies: Working out at the gym, jogging and playing basketball.
</P>
<P>
   Quote of the Day: (on Microsoft's ongoing anti-trust suit): ``We
didn't do anything wrong. We are going to defend ourselves and keep
on making software.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
