<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-SPOT-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following for
clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of Wednesday, June
9, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call Veronica
Villarreal at (206) 448-8342.
</P>
<P>
   FARM WORKERS (Seattle) _ Just two weeks before migrant workers
will begin plucking cherries from eastern Washington trees, the
federal government has decided that Washington's plans to allow
tent camps to be provided for workers on growers' properties is
illegal. The new tent camp regulations were part of a package to
create more farm worker housing that Gov. Gary Locke won
overwhelming approval for this year and were supposed to be the
first step in preventing housing crisis like the one last summer on
Wentachee's Stemilt Hill.
</P>
<P>
   By Heath Foster. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   ATM-SCAM (Seattle) _ Police say there's been a rash of bad guys
stealing ATM cards and an hour later calling the victim to say
they're security officers or police detectives who have found the
stolen card and need to have the PIN number to verify it, etc.
Clueless victims give out the PIN number and their accounts are
then emptied. Most often victimized are office receptionists who
are distracted into leaving their desks momentarily, while the
thief helps himself to the purse or wallet or sometimes just the
card.
</P>
<P>
   By Jane Hadley. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   ADOBE SYSTEMS (Seattle) _ Adobe Systems Inc. on Tuesday
announced the company is expanding and centralizing its Internet
product management and marketing efforts in Seattle. The company,
which just announced it is cutting some positions in California,
(and 10 sales jobs here), said it is launching a recruiting drive
in Seattle on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   By John Cook. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   RAMSEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ Corporate gadfly John Chevedden
sponsors votes at Paccar, Airborne Expess and Boeing calling for
changes in corporate governance. It's usually tilting at windmills
_ but not always.
</P>
<P>
   By Bruce Ramsey. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Denver) _ Seattle plays the Colorado Rockies.
</P>
<P>
   By Tyler Kepner. W/ MARINERS NOTEBOOK.
</P>
<P>
   (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS-NOTEBOOK _ Notebook items from Tuesday's game.
</P>
<P>
   By Tyler Kepner. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
