   KOSOVO-SCENE (Kosovo Polje, Yugoslavia) _ Unlike Serbs who may
live in more isolated villages, Serbs who live only a few miles
from the capital, Pristina, are not ready to leave their homes and
businesses and begin new lives as refugees. Some have no intention
of leaving Kosovo, but in the last few days other Serbs have begun
to depart. Two young men, Aleksandar Zivicand and Milan Stanovic,
say they are very nervous. ``Life might become impossible here,''
Zivic said. Why? ``Because the Albanians will be on top.'' And what
might they do? Stanovic said: ``Maybe worse things than what we did
to them.'' By Steven Erlanger. (The story has moved in ``i'' news
file.)
