   (NYT4) ST. PETER'S, Montserrat -- June 8, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN.,
JUNE 13 -- MONTSERRAT-EXPATS-COX-2, 6-8 -- Nancy Burke and her
husband Richard Hermany, both from New York City, by their 42-foot
swimming pool on a villa they purchased seven years ago for less
than $100,000. ``We couldn't afford to live like this back in the
states,'' said Hermany. Hundreds of expatriates live on Montserrat
year-round, mostly in a northern ``safe zone'' which offers some
protection from the Soufriere Hills volcano which erupted in 1995
and left most of the island covered in volcanic ash. (Rick
McKay/Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) ST. PETER'S, Montserrat -- June 8, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN.,
JUNE 13 -- MONTSERRAT-EXPATS-COX-1, 6-8 -- David Lea, from Warren,
