treehouse-like dwelling which is also home to their three children.
Hundreds of expatriates either spend winters on Montserrat, or live
here year-round, mostly in a northern ``safe zone'' which offers
some protection from the Soufriere Hills volcano which erupted in
1995 and left most of the island covered in volcanic ash. (Rick
