month. For decades Montserrat was dubbed the Emerald Isle. The
reference was, in part, a nod to the tropical lushness that for
years attracted upscale tourists. But all that changed in July 1995
when Montserrat's long-smoldering volcano blew its stack. (Rick
McKay/Cox News Service) LITE
</P>
