<SLUG> BC-LOUIMA-OFFICER-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CONVICTED OFFICER HAD CAREER OF HIGHS AND LOWS 
</HEADLINE>
  (With LOUIMA-TRIAL and LOUIMA-REACT) 
(mk) 
 By VIVIAN S. TOY   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ The police career of Charles Schwarz, the 33-year-old
officer convicted Tuesday of holding down Abner Louima while Justin
Volpe shoved a stick into his rectum, was one of extreme highs and
lows.
</P>
<P>
   In 10 years as a transit officer and a police officer, he
distinguished himself among his peers, receiving 11 medals for
meritorious and excellent police duty.
</P>
<P>
   But in 1992, while still on probation after transferring to the
Police Department from the Transit Police, he was suspended for 15
days after the department found him guilty of brutality for
punching someone in the face while he was off duty.
</P>
<P>
   When Schwarz was first indicted in the Louima case in 1997,
Police Commissioner Howard Safir told reporters that the officer
should have been dismissed after the 1992 brutality incident.
</P>
<P>
   Schwarz was also the subject of three complaints to the Civilian
Complaint Review Board: excessive force, ethnic slurs and cursing.
All three charges stemmed from the same incident and all were ruled
unsubstantiated for lack of evidence.
</P>
<P>
   Schwarz joined the Transit Police in 1989 and, after moving to
the Police Department in 1991, worked mostly at the 70th Precinct
in Brooklyn. He spent two years working in plainclothes for the
Anti-Crime unit.
</P>
<P>
   Schwarz lives in the borough of Staten Island with his wife,
Andra, near his mother and younger brother. Friends said he spent a
great deal of spare time helping his brother, who was paralyzed
when he dove into a pool in 1996. A former Marine who was also in
the Coast Guard reserves, Schwarz is an avid sports fan who played
on the 70th Precinct softball team.
</P>
<P>
   Now, having been convicted of involvement in the sexual assault
of Louima, Schwarz faces a maximum of life in prison without
parole. He is expected to appeal.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-08-99 2214EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
